HEADWORD: Wattling
<hw>Wat"tling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process
of binding or platting with twigs; also, the network so
formed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Made with a <qex>wattling</qex> of canes or sticks.</q>
